# National deployment profile (MboaShield 2030 T5)

Copy into production `.env` or Render secret group. This is the **government default**.

```bash
DEPLOYMENT_PROFILE=national
AUTH_ENFORCE=true
MBOASHIELD_ENV=production
MFA_ENFORCE=true
CORS_ORIGINS=https://trust.example.gov.cm
TRUSTED_HOSTS=trust.example.gov.cm
JWT_SECRET=<inject-from-kms>
WEBHOOK_SIGNING_SECRET=<inject-from-kms>
ANNOUNCEMENT_SIGNING_KEY=<inject-from-kms>
VAULT_SIGNING_KEY=<inject-from-kms>
DATABASE_URL=postgresql+psycopg://...
COUNTRY_PACK=cm
TENANT_ID=cm
INTEROP_ENABLED=true
```

Do **not** set soft-auth flags in national mode. See `docs/manuals/KMS_AND_SECRETS.md` and `deploy/sql/rls_tenant.sql`.
